title: Gap
content:
Gap may refer to:

  • The distance in which a player killer or bounty hunter is too far away to attack someone with Ranged or Magic (i.e. The player or victim who cannot be attacked in this situation is said to have "gap" over the attacker.)
  • The hole in a bridge inside Gu'Tanoth

Agility obstacle[edit | edit source]

  • The Gaps found within the Abyss.
  • The Gaps found within the Agility Pyramid.
  • The Gap found within the Al Kharid Rooftop Course.
  • The Gaps found within the Ardougne Rooftop Course.
  • The Gaps found within the Canifis Rooftop Course.
  • The Gap found within the Draynor Village Rooftop Course.
  • The Gaps found within the Falador Rooftop Course.
  • The Gap found within the Pollnivneach Rooftop Course.
  • The Gaps found within the Rellekka Rooftop Course.
  • The Gaps found within the Seers' Village Rooftop Course.
  • The Gaps found within the Varrock Rooftop Course.
